Lingua-IT-Ita2heb

This is a module for transliterating Italian words into Hebrew.

It should be mostly useful for personal names.

At this stage this is just a work that i have begun and it is
nowhere near being fully functional or useful. You are welcome
to submit tests, though.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Lingua::IT::Ita2heb

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Lingua-IT-Ita2heb

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Lingua-IT-Ita2heb

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Lingua-IT-Ita2heb

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Lingua-IT-Ita2heb/


